---
title: Sausage Pasta Dinner with a Shallot Zucchini Risotto for Lunch
description: Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight’s dinner extras transform into tomorrow’s lunch. That’s thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). First up in this 2-in-1 recipe is a creamy sausage and mushroom pasta with lemon and tarragon for extra flavor. The next day, it becomes a creamy risotto with zucchini that says “see ya later!” to the average desk lunch. *The nutrient information for the Risotto Lunch is as follows: Calories 800, Fat 38 g, Saturated Fat 18 g, Cholesterol 165 mg, Sodium 1450 mg, Carbs 76 g, Fiber 5 g, Sugar 10 g, and Protein 43 g. The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Sausage Pasta Dinner*
