Wash and dry all produce. Adjust racks to middle and upper position and preheat
#oven{} to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted @water{} to a boil.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely dice
@red onion{1}. Pick tarragon leaves from stems and roughly chop; discard stems.
Cut @lemon{1} into wedges. Halve, peel, and quarter @shallots{2}, then place on
a large piece of #aluminum foil{} and toss with @salt{}, @pepper{}, 1 TBSP
@balsamic vinegar{3%teaspoon} (we sent more), and a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Wrap and seal foil around shallots to create a packet. Place on a #baking sheet{}
and roast in oven on upper rack until softened, about ~{25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, stir together 3 cups water and 2 @chicken stock concentrate{3} in a
#medium bowl{}. Microwave on high for ~{1%minute}. (TIP: Alternatively, bring
mixture to a boil in a small pot.)

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add half the
onion and all of the @Arborio rice{3/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until translucent,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir stock into pan. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a simmer.
Cover pan with a #lid{} or foil and bake in oven on middle rack until rice is
al dente, ~{20-25%minutes}. (TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer contents
of pan to a small #baking dish{} before covering.)

Once water boils, add @Gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, about ~{11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta water,
then drain well.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in another large pan over medium-high heat. Remove
@Italian chicken sausage mix{18%ounce} from casings. Add to pan, breaking up
meat into pieces. Cook until browned and cooked through. Remove from pan and
set aside.

Heat 1 TBSP @butter{4%tablespoon} and another drizzle of olive oil in same pan.
Add mushrooms and remaining onion. Cook, tossing, until tender and browned,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir remaining stock concentrate, ¼ cup pasta water, and a squeeze of lemon
juice into pan. Reduce heat to low, then stir in 1 TBSP butter, @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, and half the
@tarragon{1/4%ounce}. Stir in gemelli and half the sausage. Season with
plenty of salt and pepper. (TIP: Add a splash of pasta water if sauce is dry.)

Divide between plates and sprinkle with ¼ cup @Parmesan cheese{3/4%cup} and
remaining tarragon (to taste), then serve.

== Risotto Lunch ==

Stir 2 TBSP butter, shallots, and remaining sausage into rice. Using a
#peeler{}, shave @zucchini{1} lengthwise into ribbons, rotating until you get
to core; discard core. Stir ribbons into rice. Season with plenty of salt and
pepper.

Divide between #reusable plastic containers{} and pack with remaining
Parmesan. Keep refrigerated. When ready to eat, microwave on high until hot,
~{2-3%minutes}, then sprinkle with Parmesan.

